<h1>Interrogatives</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>


<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
The @EM{{@HI{{ikutsu}}}} is used to ask "how many" about things that are counted with
<a href="grammar-counter-tsu.html">@HI{{tsu}}</a>.
</p>

<p>
The @EM{{@HI{{nan}}}} is used with a counter to ask for "how many" for things counted with
that counter.
</p>

<p>
The @EM{{@HI{{donogurai}}-}} is used to ask about the length of time something takes.
</p>

<p>
The @EM{{@HI{{gurai}}-}} is added after quantifiers to mean "about" or "approximately".
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono @KJ{{meeting^company}}ni @KJ{{outside^country^person}}ga
      @EM{{@KJ{{what^person}}}} imasuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      How many foreigners are there in this company?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@EM{{donogurai}} @KJ{{day^book^word}}wo @KJ{{exertion^strong}}shimashitaka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      How long did you study Japanese?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{study^exam}}ni @KJ{{before^life}}ga 30@KJ{{person}}@EM{{gurai}} imasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      There are about 30 teachers in our school.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

